<L>__{exterior highway}
<A>__{we cut again to the highway. the first oncoming headlights slash at the windshield.}
<L>__{interior mary's new car}
<A>__{cutting back to mary, we can sense by the tense muscles of her face that she is driving faster. the oncoming headlights blurt at her. suddenly we hear lowery's voice, loud now and frightened, as if the anxiety in the man's voice was strong enough to break through mary's effort to keep her mind silent and her imagination blank.}
<C>__{lowery's voice}
<D>__{no! i haven't the faintest idea. as i said, i last saw your sister when she left this office on friday... she said she didn't feel well and wanted to leave early and i said she could. and that was the last i saw...}
<P>__{(a pause, a thought)}
<D>__{...wait a minute, i did see her, an hour or so later, driving...}
<P>__{(a pause, then with solemn fear)}
<D>__{ah, i think you'd better come over here to my office. quick.}
<P>__{(a pause, a click)}
<D>__{caroline, get mr. cassidy for me.}
